<task id="030" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-01 Add `outputSchema` JSON field to `sprk_analysisaction` Dataverse entity</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>029</dependencies>
    <blocks>032, 033, 034, 035</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, schema, scope</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Production Dataverse entity schema change; gates 4 downstream data migrations; FULL-rigor per CLAUDE.md Confirmation Triggers (schema change to production entity).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B-G1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches `sprk_analysisaction` entity only; sibling task 031 touches the playbook node config schema — independent file targets.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add a new `outputSchema` JSON field to the production `sprk_analysisaction` Dataverse
    entity. This field declares the action's INTRINSIC output data shape (action-fixed,
    per-action). Q5 was re-shaped this session: `outputSchema` is on the ACTION (intrinsic
    data shape); `destination` + `widgetType` go on the playbook NODE config (per-playbook
    routing — see sibling task 031). The combination lets `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
    render schema-aware output (array → bullets; object → labeled key-value blocks) and
    lets `DeliverOutput` route per-playbook without changing the action.

    This is a schema-only addition. No existing column or relationship is modified. The
    field is `Edm.String` (or `Memo`) holding a JSON Schema document describing the
    action's output fields. Existing actions default to NULL during deployment; tasks 032
    through 035 populate the field for the 4 actions in the Q5 migration scope
    (`summarize-document-for-chat@v1`, `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`,
    matter-prefill, project-prefill).

    Schema change to a production Dataverse entity is a CLAUDE.md Confirmation Trigger.
    The agent MUST pause and confirm with the user before applying the change. The
    migration script MUST be idempotent — re-running on an environment that already has
    the column is a no-op. This task does NOT modify BFF code, so publish-size delta is
    zero (confirm in task notes).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Senior Dataverse schema engineer with deep familiarity
    with `sprk_analysisaction`, the existing scope library (Actions/Skills/Knowledge/Tools),
    the JPS pipeline, and the existing scope schema conventions (SYS-/CUST-/inheritance).
    Comfortable applying Web API + PowerShell schema mutations via the
    `dataverse-create-schema` skill against production-shape entities.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_analysisaction` entity has a new `sprk_outputschema` column (Memo / Edm.String
    holding JSON Schema) deployed to Spaarke Dev. The migration script is committed
    to the repo, idempotent (safe to re-run), and ships with a verification query
    (`/api/data/v9.2/sprk_analysisactions?$select=sprk_actioncode,sprk_outputschema&amp;$top=5`)
    that confirms the field is present and queryable. Existing rows have NULL in the
    new field; downstream tasks 032-035 populate it.
  </goal>

