  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">**Schema change escalation gate per CLAUDE.md Confirmation Triggers; user confirmation required at start of task.** Production Dataverse entity (`sprk_analysisaction`) is being modified — agent MUST pause and confirm with the user before applying the schema change.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-027">Dataverse solution management — `sprk_outputschema` field added via unmanaged solution conventions; deployment script under `scripts/` or `infra/dataverse/`; idempotent.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Tenant isolation — `outputSchema` is action-scoped (action-fixed shape) and not tenant-keyed; no `tenantId` required on this field. Standard scope SYS-/CUST- ownership applies via existing `sprk_analysisaction.sprk_scopetype` and ownership columns; do NOT add a parallel ownership column.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — this task adds Dataverse schema only; no BFF code or NuGet package change. Publish-size delta = 0 MB; confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — no service registration changes; confirmed N/A.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-27">Q5 RE-SHAPED: `outputSchema` is on the ACTION (intrinsic data shape) — NOT on node config. `destination` + `widgetType` go on node config (task 031). This task adds ONLY `outputSchema` to `sprk_analysisaction`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-08">11 production node executors UNMODIFIED. `DeliverOutput` is the consumer of node config `destination`/`widgetType` (task 031); the executor itself is not modified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Migration script MUST be idempotent — re-running on an environment where the column already exists succeeds with no destructive effect.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Field type: JSON content stored as `Edm.String` / Memo (length sufficient for non-trivial JSON Schema, e.g., 10K-100K chars). Document the chosen length and rationale in task notes.</constraint>
  </constraints>

