    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Dataverse column add via Web API" location=".claude/skills/dataverse-create-schema/SKILL.md">
        Use Web API + PowerShell to add columns the PAC CLI cannot create. Pattern: build
        a `Microsoft.Dynamics.CRM.MemoAttributeMetadata` payload with SchemaName
        `sprk_OutputSchema`, LogicalName `sprk_outputschema`, MaxLength sufficient for
        JSON Schema documents, RequiredLevel = None. POST to
        `/api/data/v9.2/EntityDefinitions(LogicalName='sprk_analysisaction')/Attributes`.
        Check existence first with a GET; if present, skip POST (idempotency).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Idempotent migration script" location="scripts/">
        Schema migrations under `scripts/` follow the pattern: load environment via
        Connect-MgGraph or PAC CLI; query existing metadata; conditionally apply changes;
        log results. Re-running MUST be safe.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Q5 was re-shaped this session in R6 design refinement. The original spec FR-27 put
      `renderingDestination`/`widgetType`/`widgetSchema` all on `sprk_analysisaction`. The
      re-shape splits this cleanly: actions have an intrinsic OUTPUT shape (`outputSchema`)
      that is the SAME for every playbook using the action; playbook NODES route to a
      destination (chat / workspace / form-prefill / side-effect) and pick a `widgetType`
      where applicable — that is per-playbook config, not per-action. This task ships ONLY
      the action-side field. Task 031 ships the node-side fields.

      R5 SC-18 surfaced two rendering bugs the schema-aware widget will fix:
      `tldr: string[]` rendered as raw streaming JSON tokens; `entities: { orgs, persons }`
      rendered as raw JSON object literal. With `outputSchema` declared per action and a
      schema-aware widget (task 040 + 041), the renderer accumulates token deltas, parses
      on `streaming_complete`, and dispatches per-field-type formatting.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/Add-OutputSchemaField.ps1 (NEW — migration script)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysisaction-outputschema.json (NEW — column metadata)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-030-schema-deployment-evidence.md (NEW — deployment evidence)</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <related-work>
      <item>Sibling task 031 (B-G1) adds `destination` + `widgetType` to playbook NODE config schema — independent surface; runs in parallel with this task.</item>
      <item>Downstream tasks 032-035 populate `outputSchema` on 4 existing actions; depend on this column existing.</item>
      <item>Task 040 + 041 update `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` to READ `outputSchema` at render time and dispatch array/object rendering.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context usage. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then request `/compact`.
      Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Production Dataverse entity schema change; CLAUDE.md Confirmation Trigger;
                 gates 4 downstream data migrations
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: all 11 steps below including Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```

      Read project CLAUDE.md "Confirmation Triggers" section. **PAUSE and confirm with
      user before proceeding** that adding `sprk_outputschema` to `sprk_analysisaction`
      is approved.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`; confirm task 030 status is 🔲; dependencies (029) is
      complete. Read `current-task.md` to verify no prior R6 task is in flight.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract from
      `scope-architecture.md`: how Memo columns are typed in scope entities. Read
      ADR-027 for solution management conventions. Read the dataverse-create-schema skill
      for the Web API + PowerShell pattern.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design the Field Metadata">
      Determine: SchemaName = `sprk_OutputSchema`; LogicalName = `sprk_outputschema`;
      Type = Memo; MaxLength = e.g. 100000 (justify in notes); RequiredLevel = None;
      DisplayName = "Output Schema (JSON)"; Description = "JSON Schema describing the
      action's intrinsic output data shape; consumed by StructuredOutputStreamWidget for
      schema-aware rendering". Document choices in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author Migration Script">
      Create `scripts/Add-OutputSchemaField.ps1` (or equivalent). Script: (a) connects to
      Spaarke Dev; (b) GETs existing column metadata to check idempotency; (c) if absent,
      POSTs the new column definition to the entity Attributes endpoint; (d) verifies the
      column is queryable; (e) logs result.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Apply to Spaarke Dev">
      Run the script against Spaarke Dev. Capture deployment output + the verification
      query response in `notes/task-030-schema-deployment-evidence.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Idempotency">
      Re-run the script. Confirm: no error; no destructive effect; existing data
      preserved. Capture the second run output.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Query Surface">
      Issue `GET /api/data/v9.2/sprk_analysisactions?$select=sprk_actioncode,sprk_outputschema&amp;$top=5`
      via PAC CLI or `Invoke-RestMethod`. Confirm response shape: `sprk_outputschema` field
      present, NULL for all existing rows.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Confirm BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      Confirm in task notes: BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB. No BFF code modified; no
      NuGet package added.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and record evidence in task
      notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the migration script + metadata JSON. Run
      `adr-check` skill; verify ADR-027 (solution management), ADR-029 (publish hygiene
      delta = 0), ADR-010 (DI minimalism — N/A). Both gates MUST pass before marking
      complete.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 030 🔲 → ✅. Reset
      `current-task.md` to next pending task per CLAUDE.md §7. Report completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

